    "client_msg_id": "c0efb183-1891-474f-85ce-d38cd7d30498",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "First impression is again disappointing. The installation instructions contain obvious mistakes, and then the tutorial refers to a non-existing Web page.\nThe various videos are worth watching to get the idea, but the implementation is mostly a source of frustration.\nFor those who tried it out: to uninstall, you need to delete `~/.xsh` and `~/.xiki` , both of which are created silently when you first run `xsh`. And you must remove the line appended to `.zshrc` (or its bash equivalent), which says `source ~/.xsh`.",
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "ts": "1593013706.426900",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
